ZH: 我的背很疼。
EN: My back is hurting.

ZH: 他背着一只背包去上班。
EN: He goes to work with a backpack on his back.

ZH: 她把书包背在肩膀上。
EN: She carries her backpack on her shoulders.

ZH: 孩子们背着书包走路。
EN: The children walk with their backpacks on their backs.

ZH: 这个箱子太重，我背不动。
EN: This box is too heavy for me to carry on my back.

ZH: 我的背肩困的时候，我喜欢做瑜伽来舒缓。
EN: When my back and shoulders are tired, I like to do yoga to relax.

ZH: 每次弯腰的时候我们的背都需要受到保护。
EN: Our backs need to be protected every time we bend over.

ZH: 不要长时间保持弯腰姿势，会对背不好。
EN: Do not maintain a bent-over position for a long time, as it is bad for your back.

ZH: 老人常说“宝贝儿，别痛扭背”。
EN: Elderly people often say "Take care not to twist your back, darling."

ZH: 他背了很多责任。
EN: He shoulders a lot of responsibility.

ZH: 在英文里，我们用“the back of the chair”描述椅子的背。
EN: In English, we use "the back of the chair" to describe the chair's back.

ZH: 老师后背被太阳晒红了。
EN: The teacher's back got sunburned.

ZH: 这个背包是我旅行的好伴侣。
EN: This backpack is a great companion for my travels.

ZH: 他总是背着电脑上班。
EN: He always carries his laptop on his back to work.

ZH: 我让她背着书本去图书馆。
EN: I asked her to carry the books on her back to the library.

ZH: 弯腰的时候别弯曲你的背。
EN: When bending over, do not arch your back.

ZH: 我想要一个背影温暖的拥抱。
EN: I long for a warm hug from behind.

ZH: 他被背叛的感觉很难受。
EN: He feels terrible about being betrayed.

ZH: 走路要挺直背。
EN: Walk with a straight back.

ZH: 妈妈教育我们要背诵诗歌。
EN: Mom taught us to memorize poems.
